25-OHD3 indicates both endogenous production and
supplementation. 25-OHD2 is an indicator of exogenous
sources such as diet or supplementation. Therapy is based on
measurement of Total 25-OHD, with levels <20 ng/mL indicative
of Vitamin D deficiency, while levels between 20 ng/mL and
30 ng/mL suggest insufficiency. Optimal levels are
> or = 30 ng/mL.

Reviewed date:12/23/2019 09:03:05 AM
Interpretation:
Performing Lab:
Notes/Report:

td.paragraph: For someone without known diabetes, a hemoglobin A1c value
of 6.5% or greater indicates that they may have diabetes
and this should be confirmed with a follow-up test.
For someone with known diabetes, a value <7% indicates
that their diabetes is well controlled and a value greater
than or equal to 7% indicates suboptimal control. A1c
targets should be individualized based on duration of
diabetes, age, co-morbid conditions and other considerations.
Currently, no consensus exists for use of hemoglobin A1c
for diagnosis of diabetes for children.

td.paragraph: 72 y/o male with type 1 DM, diagnosed in 1982 based on polyuria, polydipsia and neuropathy. He has been on an insulin pump since 2003 and has been very pleased with his glycemic control. Checks FS at least 7x/day due to fluctuating glucose levels. + Retinopathy, s/p laser. + Neuropathy. No known CAD. Following with Dr. Engel for ophthal (appt 4/2017), had cataract surgery by Dr. Plotycia in Nov 2015. Also saw Dr. Troia for hammer toe. Erections have improved a bit since stopping Avodart (viagra works).
He also has hypothyroidism; changed from AT to LT4 based on insurance.
A1c 6.4%. Normal TSH. LDL at goal. No proteinuria. Eosinophils wnl.
Injecting in his thighs and FS values have been harder to get down; will adjust site and monitor closely.
Saw an ENT, recommended sinus surgery, but he will hold off since no symptoms.

6/28/17: Saw Dr. Engel, improved retinopathy. Had sleep study in Spring 2017, low end of spectrum for apnea, will cont without CPAP for now. Sciatica has improved. Doing Yoga again, which he enjoys. Has follow up with Dr. Neufeld this weekend. A1c 6.8%; had a few weeks of unexplained high glucose values, but now back to baseline.
9/26/17: A1c 6.5%; feeling well overall. Doing some yoga. Going to follow up with Dr. Troia for podiatry mgmt. TFTs wnl.

1/8/18: Following with Dr. Plotycia; planning another cataract surgery. Colonoscopy via Dr. Palma; + polyps, going to follow up. FS values now back in range; he inc'd the daytime basal by about 40%. Continues to monitor closely. Getting orthotics via Dr. Troia for arthritis. A1c 6.8%, normal TFTs.

4/10/18: Overall improved; off protonix. Occassional GERD. Following with Dr. Plotycia, going this week (s/p additional laser). Waiting for orthotics to come in from Dr. Troia. A1c 6.8%. Normal TFTs. Normal PSA (going to see Dr. Norbert).

6/26/18: Feeling well overall. Has needed a higher dose of insulin at times. A1c 6.5%, LDL 78, creat wnl. Walking 10K steps per day. Had laser via Dr. Engel. Still waiting on orthotics from Dr. Troia. + GERD; followed by Dr. Palma. Would be interested in CGM and/or medtronic 670.
9/18/18: Feeling well overall. Going to see Raya this week to discuss dexcom. A1c 6.7%, TFTs wnl. Still waiting on orthotics from Dr. Troia. Plans to exercise more. Has been doing yoga.
10/1/18-placed dexcom last week but the transmitter died so pt is back to place a new dexcom

12/18/18: Wearing the dexcom which has been very useful. Has medtronic pump still; will be due for an upgrade in 2020. Going to follow up with Dr. Troia. Ophthal follow, Dr. Engel, no retinopathy in left eye, + cataract. A1c 6.6%. TFTs wnl.

3/19/19: Had a follow up with Dr. Baskin; lisinopril changed to irbesartan due to a cough which resolved. Also taking protonix which has helped cough. Also had a follow up with Dr. Frankenberger. Loving the dexcom. A1c 6.6%. LDL 69.

4/24/19: Was hospitalized at MSW after he passed out from hypoglycemia on Sat night; was in the hospital for 4 days; had CXR and CT head which was wnl. Saw Dr. Bernstein while inpatient; dec'd carb ratio to 1:10. Dexcom not set for hypoglycemia?

6/19/19-here for pump adjustment, was in the hostpital for 3d due to hypoglycemia few weeks ago, was unresponsive so his girlfriend called an ambulance. His took a bolus but didn't eat right away and had a low. Does have a dexcom.
7/18/19- started using bolus wizard but having highs 2hPP and is correcting frequently.
10/24/19-using dexcom and pump, still afraid of low so suspends pump overnight. Seen cardiac 2m ago had stress test neg
2/17/20- still having trouble sleeping,sometimes not sleeping for days, started using valerian root which does help but has appt this friday for sleep clinic. Using dexcom and pump .
4/12/20-doing much better since correcting more and not keeping his sugars high to prevent lows. Started Dexcom G6 now. Less lows.
6/16/20- diag with sleep apnea, has difficulty concentrating and sleeping. He did get his CPAP machine but didn't start using it yet. Due to sleeping issues his sugars are not as well controlled.

9/22/20- still having issues with sleep, using CPAP occasionally, was given Ambien but was afraid of SE so not using it. His tsh came back high- he ran out of meds for 3-4d which was around the same time. Sugar are higher as well, he gained 12lbs while not being as active.
11/19/20 had UTI was in the hospital for 5d - took antibiotics and is feeling better now. Using dexcom and medtronic, sugars are better lately. Going for cataract surgery this week.
2/3/21- got CPAP machine, doing better with it- sleeping more, got his first Covid vaccine, feeling good otherwise, using dexcom and pump.
5/5/21- stopped using CPAP since he wasn't using it and Medicare took it away. Using dexcom and medtronic sugars are better, recent A1c 7.1. Had stress test 6m ago.
8/4/21- will be applying for Tslim, feeling fatiqued lately since not sleeping well at night due to frequent urination, might be going for surgery, using dexcom and medtronic.
10/12/21-switched to Tslimpump with control IQ but after 3d sugars are very high and he can't seem to cotrol it, using dexcom and correcting but still running in 300's
10/26/21-sugars have improved since last visit, he was not inserting his canula correctly and was eating even at 100 thinking it was too low.
12/14/21- has been dizzy and fatiqued lately with some sob, using Tslim - doing better, no hypo's, still some high PP after dinner. Cologuard neg.

3/2/22- seeing Pulmonologist Dr. Tilly, going for CT of the lungs today- . Having SOB still. Seeing Dr. Frankel as well. BP has improved since Tamsulosin dose was decreased. He started taking protein shakes.

10/3/22- was in the hospital since April for Lung Ca. While in the hospital he went off the pump due to delirium. Had multiple infections, UTI and Pneumonia. Started RT and chemo. Was started on steroids for covid and had a bad reaction to second chemo infusion. Has been off the pump and on novolog only.
11/10/22- was in the hospital again for pneumonia - came out last week. Still didn't start the pump, on Lantus 14u and novolog 10u with each meal.
1/10/23-feeling better on the pump control IQ, last few weeks it's been higher due to issue with pump upgrade. He also was diagnosed with Shingles since last week.
2/21/23-seen Pulmonologist, prednisone dose was decreased to 5mg which might be stopped altogether eventually. Using Tslim and dexcom. Sugars are better lately.

td.paragraph: 72 y/o male with type 1 DM, diagnosed in 1982 based on polyuria, polydipsia and neuropathy. He has been on an insulin pump since 2003 and has been very pleased with his glycemic control. Checks FS at least 7x/day due to fluctuating glucose levels. + Retinopathy, s/p laser. + Neuropathy. No known CAD. Following with Dr. Engel for ophthal (appt 4/2017), had cataract surgery by Dr. Plotycia in Nov 2015. Also saw Dr. Troia for hammer toe. Erections have improved a bit since stopping Avodart (viagra works).
He also has hypothyroidism; changed from AT to LT4 based on insurance.
A1c 6.4%. Normal TSH. LDL at goal. No proteinuria. Eosinophils wnl.
Injecting in his thighs and FS values have been harder to get down; will adjust site and monitor closely.
Saw an ENT, recommended sinus surgery, but he will hold off since no symptoms.
